WEBVTT

00:01.114 --> 00:03.114
[bright tone]

00:04.573 --> 00:07.156
[sweeping orchestration]

00:07.239 --> 00:09.989
[artillery fire]

00:10.073 --> 00:13.406
[men shouting]

00:14.865 --> 00:17.948
[soldiers grunting]

00:18.031 --> 00:24.406
♪ ♪

00:25.907 --> 00:28.823
[artillery fire,
men shouting continues]

00:28.907 --> 00:35.948
♪ ♪

00:44.948 --> 00:48.031
- This is the story
of a boy and his dream.

00:48.114 --> 00:49.531
But more than that,

00:49.615 --> 00:52.073
it is the story
of an American boy

00:52.156 --> 00:55.698
and a dream
that is truly American.

00:55.782 --> 00:58.698
[soldiers shouting]

00:58.782 --> 01:01.740
[dramatic music]

01:01.823 --> 01:06.865
♪ ♪

01:06.948 --> 01:09.031
- What's the matter?
Where ya goin', Black boy?

01:09.114 --> 01:10.698
- Black boy,
we're the welcoming committee.

01:10.782 --> 01:11.698
- You'd better
get outta here.

01:11.782 --> 01:12.907
- No, Daddy.
- Go on.

01:12.989 --> 01:15.948
It just makes it tougher
having you here.

01:16.031 --> 01:18.948
[eerie music]

01:19.031 --> 01:24.073
♪ ♪

01:24.156 --> 01:27.156
[battlefield sounds fade]

01:35.657 --> 01:37.406
- The year, 1928.

01:37.490 --> 01:39.406
The time, spring.

01:39.490 --> 01:40.740
If you were a young man,

01:40.823 --> 01:43.740
your thoughts were undoubtedly
turning to those of love.

01:43.823 --> 01:45.573
But if you were a young boy,

01:45.657 --> 01:47.740
your thoughts
were of one thing...

01:47.823 --> 01:50.239
baseball.

01:50.323 --> 01:51.948
- [speaks in foreign language]

01:52.031 --> 01:53.740
[dramatic musical sting]

01:53.823 --> 01:55.865
[loud cracking]

01:57.531 --> 02:00.114
[snarling, screeching]

02:00.198 --> 02:03.031
[creature howls]

02:03.114 --> 02:05.989
[triumphant music]

02:06.073 --> 02:11.823
♪ ♪

02:11.907 --> 02:14.948
- I got ya, kid.

02:15.031 --> 02:18.782
[dramatic music]

02:18.865 --> 02:21.615
- ♪ And hopin'
we'll meet again ♪

02:21.698 --> 02:24.657
♪ Oh,
life would be a dream ♪

02:24.740 --> 02:26.615
♪ If I could take you up
in paradise ♪

02:26.698 --> 02:28.156
- Just going over
another bridge

02:28.239 --> 02:30.490
named after
some dead slave owner.

02:30.573 --> 02:32.615
Finally made it
to the promised land.

02:32.698 --> 02:34.948
Hallelujah. Amen.

02:35.031 --> 02:39.031
- Good riddance
to old Jim Crow.

02:39.114 --> 02:43.365
- ♪ If only all my precious
plans would come true ♪

02:43.448 --> 02:45.615
♪ If you would let me
spend my whole life ♪

02:45.698 --> 02:46.823
♪ Loving you ♪

02:46.907 --> 02:50.490
singers: ♪ Life could be
a dream, sweetheart ♪

02:50.573 --> 02:52.823
♪ Life could be a dream ♪

02:52.907 --> 02:56.615
♪ If only all my precious
plans would come true ♪

02:56.698 --> 02:59.615
♪ If you let me spend-- ♪
[clattering]

02:59.698 --> 03:01.156
[engine stuttering]
- ♪ Life could be a dream ♪

03:01.239 --> 03:03.531
♪ Dream, dream, dream,
d-d-dream ♪

03:13.531 --> 03:14.865
- Damn.

03:14.948 --> 03:17.948
[overlapping chatter]

03:22.406 --> 03:25.281
- I heard a noise before...

03:29.448 --> 03:32.406
[suspenseful music]

03:32.490 --> 03:39.448
♪ ♪

03:42.573 --> 03:43.615
- All right, folks,
this is our ride

03:43.698 --> 03:44.865
into the next town.

03:44.948 --> 03:46.865
Let's get our luggage
and load up.

03:46.948 --> 03:53.948
♪ ♪

04:12.448 --> 04:14.406
- Okay, ma'am,
just--here you go.

04:14.490 --> 04:15.573
Very carefully, very carefully.

04:15.657 --> 04:16.782
- Thank you.

04:16.865 --> 04:22.281
♪ ♪

04:22.365 --> 04:24.031
- Let me get those for you.

04:24.114 --> 04:27.114
[crickets chirping]

04:36.281 --> 04:37.239
- Tell me.

04:37.323 --> 04:39.365
What's that book
you been readin' about?

04:39.448 --> 04:42.573
- "A Princess of Mars"?
- Mm-hmm.

04:42.657 --> 04:45.782
- It's about this man
named John Carter...

04:45.865 --> 04:47.281
who goes from being a captain
in the army

04:47.365 --> 04:50.281
of Northern Virginia
to becoming a Martian warlord.

04:50.365 --> 04:51.615
- Huh.

04:51.698 --> 04:53.281
- Starts with him
running from Apaches

04:53.365 --> 04:54.698
and hiding
in this magical cave,

04:54.782 --> 04:57.281
which transports him
to the Red Planet.

04:57.365 --> 04:58.490
That's when it starts
to get good.

04:58.573 --> 05:00.281
- Hold on.

05:00.365 --> 05:03.448
You said the hero
was a Confederate officer.

05:03.531 --> 05:05.448
- Ex-Confederate.

05:05.531 --> 05:07.740
- He fought for slavery.

05:07.823 --> 05:10.073
You don't get to put
an "ex" in front of that.

05:10.156 --> 05:12.281
- Stories are like people.

05:12.365 --> 05:13.615
Loving them
doesn't make them perfect.

05:13.698 --> 05:16.907
You just try and cherish 'em,

05:16.989 --> 05:18.907
overlook their flaws.

05:18.989 --> 05:21.573
- Yeah, but the flaws
are still there.

05:21.657 --> 05:22.782
- Yeah, they are.

05:22.865 --> 05:25.323
But I love pulp stories.
[chuckles]

05:25.406 --> 05:28.031
I love that the heroes
get to go on adventures

05:28.114 --> 05:29.865
in other worlds,

05:29.948 --> 05:32.198
defy insurmountable odds,

05:32.281 --> 05:36.198
defeat the monster,
save the day.

05:36.281 --> 05:38.156
Little Negro boy
from the southside of Chicago

05:38.239 --> 05:40.615
don't notoriously
to get to do that.

05:40.698 --> 05:43.406
- Unless they join the army.

05:43.490 --> 05:46.490
- I didn't join for adventure.
- Hmm.

05:46.573 --> 05:49.198
- I joined
to get away from my father.

05:49.281 --> 05:50.989
Which is the real funny part,
'cause he's also

05:51.073 --> 05:53.823
now the reason
I'm coming back home.

05:53.907 --> 05:55.073
- Is he sick?

05:57.490 --> 05:59.490
- He's gone missing.

05:59.573 --> 06:02.490
[suspenseful music]

06:02.573 --> 06:09.782
♪ ♪

06:10.490 --> 06:13.865
[Etta James' "I Just Want
to Make Love to You"]

06:13.948 --> 06:15.031
♪ ♪

06:15.114 --> 06:18.031
[kids shouting playfully]

06:18.114 --> 06:20.865
♪ ♪

06:20.948 --> 06:23.031
- ♪ I don't want you ♪

06:23.114 --> 06:25.698
♪ To be no slave ♪

06:25.782 --> 06:27.698
♪ I don't want you ♪

06:27.782 --> 06:30.198
♪ To work all day ♪

06:30.281 --> 06:32.531
♪ But I want you ♪

06:32.615 --> 06:34.281
♪ To be true ♪

06:34.365 --> 06:37.865
♪ And I just
want to make love to you ♪

06:37.948 --> 06:41.198
- What are you looking at,
George Freeman?

06:41.281 --> 06:43.740
- My wife.

06:43.823 --> 06:46.031
- And why you looking
at your wife?

06:46.114 --> 06:48.281
You waiting for her
to fix you breakfast?

06:48.365 --> 06:51.031
- I'm leaving tomorrow
on the guide trip.

06:51.114 --> 06:53.073
- I'm aware.

06:53.156 --> 06:55.448
- I'm looking
at my wife because

06:55.531 --> 06:58.239
I feel I've been spending
too much time on the road

06:58.323 --> 07:02.531
and not enough time
in bed with her.

07:02.615 --> 07:06.239
[both laughing]

07:06.323 --> 07:10.114
- Why, George Freeman,
you got me blushing before God.

07:10.198 --> 07:14.740
- If he's watching, I think
we should give him a show.

07:14.823 --> 07:18.406
- What has gotten into you?

07:18.490 --> 07:22.239
You're only gonna be gone
for a few days.

07:22.323 --> 07:25.865
Used to be you couldn't wait
to go on some grand adventure.

07:29.490 --> 07:32.490
You know, I could go.

07:34.948 --> 07:37.239
Make the trip instead of you.

07:39.198 --> 07:40.740
- You serious?

07:42.573 --> 07:44.948
- Is that idea so crazy?
- No, no.

07:45.031 --> 07:47.281
- Is it?
- No.

07:47.365 --> 07:51.490
- You know,
I've written more than my share

07:51.573 --> 07:53.490
of reviews for the guide.

07:53.573 --> 07:54.823
- Arguably, the best ones.

07:54.907 --> 07:56.406
- The best ones.
- Mm-hmm.

07:56.490 --> 07:58.782
- And all of them
based on your notes.

07:58.865 --> 08:01.948
- Oh. [chuckles]
- Now...

08:02.031 --> 08:05.323
imagine how good they could get

08:05.406 --> 08:08.114
if I could take notes
on my own.

08:08.198 --> 08:10.156
- Hmm.

08:10.239 --> 08:11.323
Mm-hmm.

08:11.406 --> 08:14.114
You know the road
is a dangerous place

08:14.198 --> 08:16.865
for a woman traveling alone.

08:16.948 --> 08:20.239
You know the shit
I deal with out there.

08:21.948 --> 08:26.156
It's dangerous out there,
Hippolyta.

08:26.239 --> 08:28.989
Where you going?

08:29.073 --> 08:30.615
- My party starts at noon,

08:30.698 --> 08:31.865
and those pecans in the kitchen

08:31.948 --> 08:34.698
are not gonna turn
themselves into pies.

08:34.782 --> 08:37.782
- Stay with me.
- [sighs]

08:40.782 --> 08:43.989
[moans]

08:44.073 --> 08:46.323
What are you doing?

08:46.406 --> 08:48.156
[moans]

08:48.239 --> 08:50.406
You know Dee is up.

08:50.490 --> 08:53.031
You know these walls are thin.

08:53.114 --> 08:55.114
[moans]

08:57.448 --> 08:58.365
- I can't remember
the last time

08:58.448 --> 09:00.698
we made love
in the light of day.

09:00.782 --> 09:04.365
I want to see my wife.

09:04.448 --> 09:06.365
[both moaning]

09:06.448 --> 09:09.365
[radio chatter]

09:09.448 --> 09:12.365
[pencil scribbling]

09:12.448 --> 09:15.406
[soft music]

09:15.490 --> 09:22.448
♪ ♪

09:45.323 --> 09:48.323
[Hippolyta moaning]

09:55.448 --> 09:57.448
- Gross.

10:05.281 --> 10:06.365
[screams]

10:06.448 --> 10:07.531
Atticus!
- Diana!

10:07.615 --> 10:09.073
[both laughing]

10:09.156 --> 10:12.073
♪ ♪

10:12.156 --> 10:13.406
What's going on?

10:13.490 --> 10:14.865
- Get over here.
- George, baby,

10:14.948 --> 10:17.239
what's going on in there?
Is that Dee?

10:17.323 --> 10:21.114
- She's fine.
She just got surprised, is all.

10:21.198 --> 10:22.782
Your nephew is back.

10:22.865 --> 10:25.573
- Oh, Tic's back!

10:25.657 --> 10:26.948
- I wasn't scared.

10:27.031 --> 10:28.740
- I know you weren't.
- You sounded scared to me.

10:28.823 --> 10:30.657
Tic's back!
Yes!

10:30.740 --> 10:33.657
[heartwarming music]

10:33.740 --> 10:40.740
♪ ♪

10:47.865 --> 10:49.406
- Thank you for your business.

10:49.490 --> 10:50.448
- Heading through that part
of the country

10:50.531 --> 10:51.448
in a couple months.

10:51.531 --> 10:52.989
I'll vet it then--
- Welcome home, Tic.

10:53.073 --> 10:54.448
- Oh, the tip is solid.

10:54.531 --> 10:56.323
My cousin bought smokes
from there just last week.

10:56.406 --> 10:58.573
- I believe, but I still
have to triple-check.

10:58.657 --> 11:03.865
A bad tip in the guidebook
gets someone killed.

11:03.948 --> 11:05.490
- Okay, I got you.

11:05.573 --> 11:08.323
[ominous music]

11:08.406 --> 11:12.448
♪ ♪

11:12.531 --> 11:17.156
- Ahh. Getting reacquainted
with old friends.

11:17.239 --> 11:18.490
- Something like that.

11:18.573 --> 11:21.198
- I'm surprised that one
caught your interest.

11:21.281 --> 11:23.865
Horror is usually my thing.

11:23.948 --> 11:26.031
- "On the Creation of Niggers."

11:27.907 --> 11:30.865
- Now that's one of Lovecraft's
we don't hear mentioned often.

11:30.948 --> 11:32.573
- Pops made me
memorize that poem

11:32.657 --> 11:34.448
word for word after
he caught me reading this.

11:34.531 --> 11:35.615
- Mm.

11:35.698 --> 11:37.365
- Thought it might turn me
from the pulp trash

11:37.448 --> 11:42.031
I borrow from here
to respectable literature.

11:42.114 --> 11:45.198
- He's been missing
about two weeks.

11:45.281 --> 11:46.531
- About?
You're not sure.

11:46.615 --> 11:48.406
- You know
how he can get on the sauce.

11:48.490 --> 11:50.198
I--I didn't think anything
of it

11:50.281 --> 11:52.865
until his landlord dropped by
when he didn't pay rent.

11:52.948 --> 11:54.698
I don't know where
he could've gone.

11:54.782 --> 11:56.031
- I might have an idea.

11:56.114 --> 11:58.073
He wrote me.

11:58.156 --> 11:59.573
About my mama.

12:01.948 --> 12:05.698
[suspenseful music]

12:05.782 --> 12:08.615
- What, uh...
wh--wh-what'd he say?

12:10.989 --> 12:14.198
- Said he found out where
her family came from.

12:14.281 --> 12:17.365
Wanted me to come home
so I could go there with him.

12:17.448 --> 12:20.573
- He's still obsessing
over her ancestry?

12:20.657 --> 12:23.698
I thought he'd given
all that up when she passed.

12:27.448 --> 12:29.907
- "I know that,
like your mother,

12:29.989 --> 12:33.907
"you think
that you can forget the past.

12:33.989 --> 12:35.615
"You can't.

12:35.698 --> 12:37.740
"The past is a living thing.

12:37.823 --> 12:39.406
"You own it--owe it.

12:39.490 --> 12:40.782
"Now I have found something

12:40.865 --> 12:42.365
"about your mother's
forebearers.

12:42.448 --> 12:44.657
"You have a sacred...

12:44.740 --> 12:47.615
secret legacy, a birthright
that's been kept from you."

12:47.698 --> 12:48.782
- That's strange;
that doesn't really even

12:48.865 --> 12:49.865
sound like your father.

12:49.948 --> 12:52.865
- I haven't even gotten
to the strange part.

12:54.823 --> 12:56.573
The place
he wants me to go with him--

12:56.657 --> 12:59.698
it's in Lovecraft Country.

12:59.782 --> 13:01.907
Letter says Mom's ancestors

13:01.989 --> 13:06.239
are from Arkham, Massachusetts.

13:08.073 --> 13:09.531
- Home of the corpse reanimator
and--

13:09.615 --> 13:11.657
- And Herbert West.

13:13.239 --> 13:16.615
- Lovecraft based it on Salem,
but that's not real.

13:16.698 --> 13:18.531
- You sure?

13:21.198 --> 13:24.031
- Let me see the letter.

13:29.490 --> 13:32.239
That's a "D."
It's not Arkham with a "K."

13:32.323 --> 13:36.073
It's Ardham with a "D".
That's a "D."

13:36.156 --> 13:43.073
♪ ♪

13:43.156 --> 13:45.657
- You know,
for someone who talked so much

13:45.740 --> 13:48.698
about the importance
of being educated,

13:48.782 --> 13:50.323
you'd think Pop would learn
how to write clearly.

13:50.406 --> 13:51.448
- I'm gonna look
into this Ardham

13:51.531 --> 13:53.948
and see if I can glean
any clues as to what this

13:54.031 --> 13:58.114
"secret legacy"
Montrose is going on about.

13:58.198 --> 14:00.281
- I-I'm serious.
[laughs]

14:00.365 --> 14:03.698
Don't delete that.

14:03.782 --> 14:06.657
[Tierra Whack's "CLONES"]

14:06.740 --> 14:08.323
♪ Everybody talkin'
like me now ♪

14:08.406 --> 14:10.365
♪ Heard I'm who
they wanna be now ♪

14:10.448 --> 14:11.823
♪ Westbound, eastbound ♪

14:11.907 --> 14:13.156
♪ Everybody walkin'
like me now ♪

14:13.239 --> 14:14.698
♪ Everybody talkin'
like me now ♪

14:14.782 --> 14:16.948
- Come on!
It won't stop.

14:17.031 --> 14:18.156
- ♪ Westbound, eastbound ♪

14:18.239 --> 14:19.823
♪ Everybody walkin'
like me now ♪

14:19.907 --> 14:21.698
♪ Everybody talkin'
like me now ♪

14:21.782 --> 14:23.323
- An adventure.

14:23.406 --> 14:25.406
An opportunity
to see the world.

14:25.490 --> 14:28.031
Just sign.

14:28.114 --> 14:29.698
- ♪ Heard I'm who
