♪ Call me God,
yeah, he kneelin' ♪

14:37.948 --> 14:39.531
♪ Audio, I'm top billin' ♪

14:39.615 --> 14:41.198
♪ All of my boys
dope dealin' ♪

14:41.281 --> 14:43.782
[train rumbling loudly]

14:49.573 --> 14:53.031
- Hey, we closin' early
for the block party.

14:53.114 --> 14:56.073
I said we're closin' early
for the block...

14:56.156 --> 14:58.198
Holy shit.
Tic, is that you?

14:58.281 --> 14:59.698
Almost didn't recognize you
without them damn

14:59.782 --> 15:01.198
Coke bottle glasses on.

15:01.281 --> 15:03.281
You remember me, Tree.
- Yeah, I remember.

15:05.573 --> 15:07.823
Listen, the guy
with the earrings, the owner--

15:07.948 --> 15:09.698
He here?

15:09.782 --> 15:12.782
- Sammy. He out back.

15:19.490 --> 15:21.490
[laughs]

15:22.365 --> 15:24.239
- [moans]

15:24.323 --> 15:25.782
- Shit. Sorry.

15:25.865 --> 15:27.865
- Oh, shit.

15:29.823 --> 15:33.156
- You're Montrose's son, right?

15:34.823 --> 15:36.239
I remember plenty of nights
you dragging him

15:36.323 --> 15:39.365
off one of my barstools.

15:39.448 --> 15:41.615
He hasn't been perched
on one in weeks.

15:43.865 --> 15:45.907
- When's the last time
you saw him?

15:45.989 --> 15:48.323
- 'Bout two weeks ago.

15:48.406 --> 15:50.073
Left here with some white man.

15:50.156 --> 15:51.615
- Was he a cop?
- Doubt it.

15:51.698 --> 15:54.615
Looked like
one of Bill Haley's Comets.

15:54.698 --> 15:57.448
Can't get the clothes he was
wearing on a pig's salary.

15:57.531 --> 15:59.782
My guess, he's a lawyer.

15:59.865 --> 16:02.073
Would explain
how he could afford the car.

16:04.365 --> 16:05.615
- You saw what he was driving?

16:05.698 --> 16:07.114
- Tree did.

16:07.198 --> 16:09.907
Said it was a silver sedan.
Something Ford.

16:09.989 --> 16:13.198
Shot off so fast,
it had to be expensive.

