17:16.615 --> 17:19.907
♪ That's all I'll ever need ♪

17:19.989 --> 17:24.531
♪ ♪

17:24.615 --> 17:26.698
Whoo!

17:26.782 --> 17:27.865
[cheers and applause]

17:27.948 --> 17:29.573
Thank you, thank you.

17:29.657 --> 17:31.657
All right, all right,
I think I got time

17:31.740 --> 17:33.198
for one more
before Slick Willie

17:33.281 --> 17:34.698
comes up with his guitar.

17:34.782 --> 17:37.406
Now, what y'all want to hear?
[overlapping chatter]

17:37.490 --> 17:40.323
Come on, y'all don't really
like that lily-white shit

17:40.406 --> 17:41.989
they play on the radio now,
do you?

17:42.073 --> 17:43.740
♪ Life could be a dream ♪

17:43.823 --> 17:46.281
Sh'boom, sh'bored.

17:46.365 --> 17:47.865
Now, let me hear something
that'll wake me up.

17:47.948 --> 17:50.823
- "Whole Lotta Shakin'"!

17:50.907 --> 17:52.365
- Is that Letitia?

17:52.448 --> 17:54.198
- Ruby, it's your sister.

17:54.281 --> 17:56.198
- Thank you, Floyd.
I have eyes.

17:56.281 --> 18:00.448
[cheers and applause]

18:00.531 --> 18:03.073
A little bit
of blues it is, then.

18:03.156 --> 18:05.573
- Leti, get up there
and sing with her.

18:05.657 --> 18:06.907
all: Leti, Leti!

18:06.989 --> 18:08.198
- Now, now.

18:08.281 --> 18:10.031
I'm sure my sister's tired

18:10.114 --> 18:12.406
from traveling in
from wherever it is

18:12.490 --> 18:14.782
she just magically
appeared from.

18:14.865 --> 18:18.239
all: Leti, Leti, Leti, Leti!

18:18.323 --> 18:20.823
[crowd chanting]

18:23.531 --> 18:26.531
[cheers and applause]

18:28.989 --> 18:30.281
- Y'all are gonna
have to bear with us.

18:30.365 --> 18:34.448
We haven't sang together
since our church days.

18:34.531 --> 18:37.031
- Sure is no secret
that those days are long gone.

18:37.114 --> 18:39.740
[laughter]

18:39.823 --> 18:41.156
- All right.

18:41.239 --> 18:43.406
"Whole Lotta Shakin'."

18:43.490 --> 18:46.782
♪ 21 drums
and an old bass horn ♪

18:46.865 --> 18:50.740
♪ And somebody beating
on a ding-dong ♪

18:50.823 --> 18:52.448
♪ ♪

18:52.531 --> 18:54.448
Come on, now.

18:54.531 --> 18:57.573
♪ ♪

18:57.657 --> 18:59.615
♪ Come on over, baby,

18:59.698 --> 19:01.281
♪ A whole lotta shakin'
going on ♪

19:01.365 --> 19:04.156
- Who's that?
- [laughs]

19:04.239 --> 19:06.865
- ♪ Come on over, baby ♪

19:06.948 --> 19:10.448
♪ Baby, you can't go wrong ♪

19:10.531 --> 19:12.239
♪ Ain't nobody fakin' ♪

19:12.323 --> 19:15.782
♪ Whole lotta shakin'
going on ♪

19:15.865 --> 19:17.782
♪ ♪

19:17.865 --> 19:20.823
- ♪ Come on over, baby,
hey! ♪

19:20.907 --> 19:24.657
♪ A whole lotta kickin'
in the barn ♪

19:24.740 --> 19:27.657
♪ Come on over, baby ♪

19:27.740 --> 19:30.657
♪ We got the bull by the horn ♪

19:30.740 --> 19:32.698
♪ Everything is kickin' ♪

19:32.782 --> 19:35.989
♪ Whole lotta shakin'
going on ♪

19:36.073 --> 19:37.907
[laughs]
- All right, now.

19:37.989 --> 19:41.323
♪ Bakin' and makin' it shake ♪

19:41.406 --> 19:44.698
♪ Door and the floor
and the gate ♪

19:44.782 --> 19:47.823
both: ♪ Bakin' it
and makin' it shake ♪

19:47.907 --> 19:51.490
- ♪ Cake and pie on the plate ♪

19:51.573 --> 19:55.156
both: ♪ Shakin' and shakin'
and shakin' the place ♪

19:55.239 --> 19:58.365
♪ Come on over, baby, come on ♪

19:58.448 --> 20:02.239
♪ We done found
that ding-dong ♪

20:03.448 --> 20:06.698
[crowd shrieking happily]

20:06.782 --> 20:13.782
♪ ♪

20:22.615 --> 20:25.323
♪ Come on over, baby ♪

20:25.406 --> 20:29.365
♪ Whole lotta shakin'
going on ♪

20:29.448 --> 20:32.198
♪ Come on over, baby ♪

20:32.281 --> 20:35.531
♪ Baby, you can't go wrong ♪

20:35.615 --> 20:37.406
♪ Ain't nobody fakin' ♪

20:37.490 --> 20:42.782
♪ Whole lotta shakin'
going on ♪

20:42.865 --> 20:45.740
[cheers and applause]

20:45.823 --> 20:48.740
- All right! All right, now!

20:48.823 --> 20:51.073
Thanks, fellas.

20:51.156 --> 20:53.281
That was fun.

20:53.365 --> 20:55.198
Yeah! [laughs]

20:55.281 --> 20:56.989
♪ ♪

20:57.073 --> 21:00.740
- ♪ We gonna ride, ride, ride
all night long ♪

21:00.823 --> 21:02.281
- Dress that short,

21:02.365 --> 21:04.198
should be wearing
some stockings.

21:04.281 --> 21:05.907
- It's too hot for all that.

21:05.989 --> 21:07.281
- You can't even
afford stockings?

21:07.365 --> 21:08.657
- Who said I can't afford 'em?

21:08.740 --> 21:10.114
- You don't need to say it;
I know you only here

21:10.198 --> 21:11.698
'cause you need money.

21:11.782 --> 21:13.740
And don't think just 'cause
you got up and sang with me

21:13.823 --> 21:15.156
that you're getting
any of these tips.

21:15.239 --> 21:16.573
- I don't need a handout, Ruby,

21:16.657 --> 21:19.073
just a place to stay
for a while.

21:19.156 --> 21:21.114
- There it is.

21:23.865 --> 21:26.573
- Who's that?

21:26.657 --> 21:27.782
- Who, Tic?

21:27.865 --> 21:29.907
- That's Tic?

21:29.989 --> 21:32.406
Skinny, glasses kid who was too
smart for his own good, Tic?

21:32.490 --> 21:34.448
- Yeah, he's grown up.

21:34.531 --> 21:36.531
More than I can say for you.

21:37.907 --> 21:39.782
I'm over at the boarding house
on McCarthy.

21:39.865 --> 21:41.615
- Oh, that place is a shithole.

21:41.698 --> 21:43.782
What happened to the room
on Linden?

21:43.865 --> 21:46.239
- Mama's funeral happened.

21:48.365 --> 21:49.615
- Ruby--
- There's nothing to read

21:49.698 --> 21:51.782
into me bringing it up.

21:51.865 --> 21:54.490
It's just facts.

21:54.573 --> 21:55.948
You can stay two nights.

21:56.031 --> 21:58.281
- And what job am I supposed
to find in two days?

21:58.365 --> 22:00.323
- You can get a job
up on the Northside.

22:00.406 --> 22:02.490
- I'm not cleaning house.
- So what then?

22:02.573 --> 22:04.073
You think you're gonna go
downtown get a job

22:04.156 --> 22:05.156
in one of those
department stores?

22:05.239 --> 22:06.156
- Yes, I do.

22:06.239 --> 22:07.156
- You think it's that easy,
huh?

22:07.239 --> 22:08.156
- Yes, I do.

22:08.239 --> 22:09.823
- You know
I've been applying for years.

22:09.907 --> 22:11.198
- Well, if I get the job,

22:11.281 --> 22:12.657
it'll be enough money
for both of us to move.

22:12.740 --> 22:14.448
- You know,
I'm fine where I am.

22:14.531 --> 22:15.698
- We could have our own rooms
for once.

22:15.782 --> 22:17.657
Hell, our own house, maybe.

22:17.740 --> 22:19.073
There's a lot
of colored folks pioneering

22:19.156 --> 22:20.531
into all-white neighborhoods
these days.

22:20.615 --> 22:24.156
- Then maybe you should ask
one them to put you up.

22:24.239 --> 22:26.989
Or go to Marvin's.

22:27.073 --> 22:29.281
Two nights, Leti.

22:29.365 --> 22:30.782
That's it.

22:30.865 --> 22:37.865
♪ ♪

22:46.989 --> 22:49.031
- Your knees still acting up?

22:49.114 --> 22:50.823
- It's a blessing
they're doing anything at all

22:50.907 --> 22:53.698
after two shattered kneecaps.

22:53.782 --> 22:55.573
And now Hippolyta got this
crazy idea

22:55.657 --> 22:56.573
to go out on the road.

22:56.657 --> 22:58.031
I can't imagine
what would happen

22:58.114 --> 22:59.490
if those crackers
had caught her

22:59.573 --> 23:02.490
outside of Anna instead of me.

23:03.490 --> 23:06.907
- That's why you publish
the guidebook, right?

23:06.989 --> 23:08.198
Keep us Negros safe.

23:08.281 --> 23:10.114
- [laughs]

23:12.448 --> 23:13.698
- Dee do this?

23:13.782 --> 23:16.573
- Kid's got imagination
like you.

23:16.657 --> 23:18.031
Terrifying, ain't they?

23:18.114 --> 23:20.989
[dramatic music]

23:21.073 --> 23:24.073
- Tell me where
I can find Ardham.

23:24.156 --> 23:26.907
- Well, now, that's gonna be
a little tricky.

23:26.989 --> 23:29.907
The last mention
of it in any census

23:29.989 --> 23:33.073
that I can find
is over two centuries ago...

23:33.156 --> 23:38.406
which puts it somewhere around
Devon County, Massachusetts.

23:38.490 --> 23:39.782
- Devon County.

23:42.448 --> 23:43.865
- You goin' after him.

23:46.657 --> 23:48.615
- I'm gonna need a car.

23:49.948 --> 23:50.948
- Woody still running?

23:51.031 --> 23:52.490
- Woody'll outlast us all.

23:52.573 --> 23:53.907
That's the only thing
I am sure of,

23:53.989 --> 23:55.615
other than that
I'm going with you.

23:55.698 --> 23:56.698
- Uncle George,
with them knees--

23:56.782 --> 24:00.114
- I was heading out
on a guide trip anyway.

24:00.198 --> 24:03.657
Devon County will be
a good addition.

24:06.531 --> 24:09.406
- You might not be so sure
about that...

24:09.490 --> 24:10.823
after you look at this.

24:12.698 --> 24:14.615
Devon County?

24:14.698 --> 24:17.657
[ominous music]

24:17.740 --> 24:24.698
♪ ♪

24:26.865 --> 24:29.865
[train rumbling]

24:35.490 --> 24:42.490
♪ ♪

24:56.114 --> 24:59.031
[gears clicking]

24:59.114 --> 25:01.698
[light whirring]

25:01.782 --> 25:03.782
[low buzzing]

25:06.073 --> 25:08.948
[jazz music]

25:09.031 --> 25:12.823
♪ ♪

25:12.907 --> 25:17.406
[train rumbling]

25:30.782 --> 25:33.823
[train rattling]

26:26.156 --> 26:29.698
[line trilling]

26:29.782 --> 26:33.239
- Where can I direct
your call?

26:33.323 --> 26:36.406
- 555-438...

26:36.490 --> 26:39.198
520...

26:39.281 --> 26:42.281
3093...

26:42.365 --> 26:46.740
2915.

26:46.823 --> 26:49.239
- South Korea?

26:49.323 --> 26:51.323
- Yes.

26:56.490 --> 26:59.740
[line trilling]

26:59.823 --> 27:01.657
- [speaks Korean]

27:03.657 --> 27:06.114
Tic?

27:06.198 --> 27:09.073
Is that you?

27:09.156 --> 27:12.073
[suspenseful music]

27:12.156 --> 27:13.657
♪ ♪

27:13.740 --> 27:16.657
You went home.

27:16.740 --> 27:19.948
♪ ♪

27:20.031 --> 27:21.698
You shouldn't have.

27:26.989 --> 27:29.989
[Leti grunting]

27:42.406 --> 27:45.448
- You just gonna stand there,
Tic, or you gonna help me?

27:45.531 --> 27:47.365
- Leti Lewis.
- [laughs]

27:47.448 --> 27:49.989
Now, only my friends
get to call me that.

27:50.073 --> 27:51.365
We still friends?

27:51.448 --> 27:53.281
- Well, considering
you were the only female member

27:53.365 --> 27:55.365
of the Southside Futurists
Science Fiction Club.

27:55.448 --> 27:59.031
- I was. [laughs]
I was.

28:00.740 --> 28:04.156
I heard you were
down in Florida hiding out.

28:04.239 --> 28:05.490
How was it?

28:05.573 --> 28:07.448
- Segregated.

28:07.531 --> 28:09.823
- Mm.
- And you, where you been?

28:09.907 --> 28:12.989
- Mm, I've been
a little bit everywhere.

28:13.073 --> 28:14.490
- Doing?

28:14.573 --> 28:16.281
- Everything.

28:16.365 --> 28:18.365
- Y'all ready to go?

28:18.448 --> 28:20.156
- Wait, you coming with us?

28:20.239 --> 28:21.198
- Part way.

28:21.281 --> 28:22.365
Marvin's working for

28:22.448 --> 28:24.031
the Springfield
African American these days.

28:24.114 --> 28:25.657
He's gonna look
into that mysterious town

28:25.740 --> 28:27.031
of Ardham for us.

28:27.114 --> 28:29.989
- Why, thank you, baby.
Are we checklist-ready?

28:30.073 --> 28:31.073
- Yep.

28:32.657 --> 28:34.531
- All right,
mattress and blankets.

28:34.615 --> 28:35.989
- Check and check.

28:36.073 --> 28:39.490
- Spare tire and jack.

28:39.573 --> 28:42.114
- Check.
- Flares and first-aid kit.

28:43.239 --> 28:45.365
- Double check.
- Reading materials.

28:45.448 --> 28:47.907
- I got that covered.
- Very well.

28:47.989 --> 28:51.989
I think the travel checklist
is complete.

28:53.907 --> 28:55.156
- Anything we're forgetting?

28:55.239 --> 28:57.782
- Oh, no,
I think that's everything.

28:58.907 --> 29:00.865
- I think
there's something missing.

29:00.948 --> 29:02.573
- You don't
have to do this every time.

29:02.657 --> 29:05.239
- Oh, that's right,
Dee's travel comic.

29:05.323 --> 29:07.198
- That's what's missing

29:07.281 --> 29:08.740
because I've been waiting
patiently to see

29:08.823 --> 29:10.448
what happens to Panther Man.

29:10.531 --> 29:11.698
- Mm-hmm.

29:15.615 --> 29:16.615
Boop.

29:21.198 --> 29:23.073
- "Orithyia Blue"?

29:23.156 --> 29:25.114
Oh, pumpkin,
you decided to change it.

29:25.198 --> 29:27.365
- It's no big deal, Ma.

29:27.448 --> 29:28.740
I will see you
when you get back, Pop.

29:28.823 --> 29:31.615
- You will, baby.
Mmm.

29:34.531 --> 29:36.365
- Oh,
and the atlas is in Woody.

29:36.448 --> 29:38.448
- Yes.

29:41.948 --> 29:45.281
Thank you, baby.
- Be safe.

29:45.365 --> 29:46.948
- Good evening.

29:47.031 --> 29:50.740
[laughter]

29:50.823 --> 29:55.823
I, um--I find myself
not for the first time

29:55.907 --> 29:58.281
in, um...

29:58.365 --> 30:00.740
the position
of a kind of Jeremiah.

30:03.406 --> 30:05.239
For example, I don't disagree
with Mr. Burford

30:05.323 --> 30:07.365
that the, um...

30:09.198 --> 30:11.239
The inequality suffered
by the American Negro

30:11.323 --> 30:12.782
population
of the United States

30:12.865 --> 30:16.114
has hindered
the American dream.

30:16.198 --> 30:17.490
Indeed, it has.

30:17.573 --> 30:20.657
I quarrel with some other
things he has to say.

30:20.740 --> 30:23.281
The other, deeper element

30:23.365 --> 30:27.657
of a certain awkwardness
I feel

30:27.740 --> 30:29.823
has to do with, um...

30:29.907 --> 30:32.490
it has to one's point of view;
I had to put it that way.

30:32.573 --> 30:36.323
One's, uh, one's sense,
one's system of reality.

30:36.406 --> 30:37.698
It would seem to me
the proposition

30:37.782 --> 30:39.490
before the House,
when I put it that way,

30:39.573 --> 30:40.823
is the American dream

30:40.907 --> 30:42.823
at the expense
of the American Negro,

30:42.907 --> 30:44.823
or the American dream
is at the expense

30:44.907 --> 30:46.823
of the American Negro...

30:46.907 --> 30:50.490
is a question
hideously loaded,

30:50.573 --> 30:52.698
and that one's response
to that question

30:52.782 --> 30:55.156
or one's reaction
to that question,

30:55.239 --> 30:56.782
has to depend on,
in effect,

30:56.865 --> 30:59.323
on where you find yourself
in the world,

30:59.406 --> 31:01.948
what your sense of reality is,

31:02.031 --> 31:04.740
what your system
of reality is.

31:04.823 --> 31:08.198
That is,
it depends on assumptions

31:08.281 --> 31:10.989
which we hold so deeply

31:11.073 --> 31:13.865
as to be scarcely aware
of them.

31:13.948 --> 31:16.865
A white South African
or a Mississippi sharecropper

31:16.948 --> 31:18.365
or a Mississippi sheriff

31:18.448 --> 31:20.907
or a Frenchman
driven out of Algeria,

31:20.989 --> 31:23.698
all have,
at bottom,

31:23.782 --> 31:28.406
a system of reality which
compels them to, for example,

31:28.490 --> 31:31.031
in the case of the French
exile from Algeria,

31:31.114 --> 31:33.907
to defend French reasons
from having ruled Algeria.

31:33.989 --> 31:36.698
The Mississippi
or the Alabama sheriff,

31:36.782 --> 31:38.365
who really does believe,
when he's facing

31:38.448 --> 31:41.365
a Negro boy or girl,
that this woman, this man,

31:41.448 --> 31:45.657
this child must be insane
to attack the system

31:45.740 --> 31:48.031
to which he owes
his entire identity.

31:48.114 --> 31:49.865
And on the other hand...

31:49.948 --> 31:51.406
- There's a diner
called Lydia's

31:51.490 --> 31:52.740
I got a tip on near here.

31:52.823 --> 31:53.907
Won't take us too far
off course

31:53.989 --> 31:54.948
to have lunch there.

31:55.031 --> 31:56.448
What do you say to a detour?

31:56.531 --> 31:59.573
- Where is it?
- Simmonsville.

31:59.657 --> 32:01.073
- You know what that area
be populated by

32:01.156 --> 32:02.865
on Diana's atlas?

32:02.948 --> 32:04.281
- What?
- Buncha trolls

32:04.365 --> 32:06.865
who pick their teeth
with unwary motorists.

32:06.948 --> 32:09.198
- Funny. I need to add
some entries to the guide.

32:09.281 --> 32:10.281
I'm on a deadline.

32:10.365 --> 32:11.615
- Aren't you the publisher?

32:11.698 --> 32:12.740
- Exactly, which is why I know

32:12.823 --> 32:14.740
how much of a hard-ass
I can be.

32:14.823 --> 32:16.907
[camera shutter clicks]

32:16.989 --> 32:18.948
- Well, not that either of you
asked my opinion,

32:19.031 --> 32:21.406
but I could use a hot meal.

32:21.490 --> 32:23.031
- You heard the girl.

32:23.114 --> 32:24.573
- Since this girl's
not allowed to drive,

32:24.657 --> 32:26.740
I'm picking the radio station.

32:26.823 --> 32:30.657
- ♪ Yes, you upsets me, baby ♪

32:30.740 --> 32:32.782
♪ Yes,
I'm telling you people ♪

32:32.865 --> 32:37.948
♪ She's something fine
that you really ought to see ♪

32:38.031 --> 32:41.114
- Let's take this next right.

32:41.198 --> 32:42.281
What you doing, girl?

32:42.365 --> 32:43.907
- I'm turning up B.B.

32:43.989 --> 32:45.531
- ♪ Man, she knocks me
out the way... ♪

32:45.615 --> 32:48.448
- What you know about B.B.?
- That's my music.

32:48.531 --> 32:51.448
- ♪ You upsets me, baby ♪
- Her music.

32:51.531 --> 32:53.989
- [Leti singing along]
♪ Yes, you upsets me, baby ♪

32:54.073 --> 32:55.448
[dogs barking]

32:55.531 --> 32:58.073
♪ Like being hit
by a falling tree ♪

32:58.156 --> 33:02.073
- ♪ Woman, woman,
what you do to me ♪

33:02.156 --> 33:05.073
[music slows and distorts]

33:05.156 --> 33:11.823
♪ ♪

33:11.948 --> 33:15.989
[train bell ringing]
- ♪ You upsets me ♪

33:16.073 --> 33:17.823
♪ Well, you upsets me, baby ♪

33:17.907 --> 33:20.823
- Now, we're looking
for a red-brick building.

33:20.907 --> 33:22.323
Should be
on the left-hand side,

33:22.406 --> 33:24.198
far end of town.

33:24.281 --> 33:26.657
- ♪ What you do to me ♪

33:26.740 --> 33:27.989
- That must be it.

33:28.073 --> 33:35.073
♪ ♪

33:38.573 --> 33:40.573
All right.

33:47.573 --> 33:49.281
- Didn't you say
it was called Lydia's?

33:49.365 --> 33:50.782
- It's in the right place.

33:50.865 --> 33:53.198
Don't judge a book
by its cover.

33:53.281 --> 33:55.531
- Book can't
refuse you service.

33:55.615 --> 33:58.198
- Or spit in your water glass.

33:58.281 --> 33:59.823
- Good afternoon.

34:01.740 --> 34:03.448
We were just driving by,
thought we'd stop in

34:03.531 --> 34:05.490
and have some lunch.

34:11.114 --> 34:12.865
We'll seat ourselves, then.

34:12.948 --> 34:14.448
[grunts]

34:14.531 --> 34:17.281
Yes, that's what we'll do.
Thank you.

34:19.114 --> 34:21.989
Menu, please?

34:28.156 --> 34:31.365
What's good here?
- Uh... uh...

34:31.448 --> 34:33.615
- Why don't we just start
with some coffees?

34:40.198 --> 34:42.907
- Looks like the Simmonsville
Dinette isn't making the guide.

34:42.989 --> 34:44.239
- Yeah, okay,
but we're here now.

34:44.323 --> 34:46.365
- Doesn't mean we have to stay.

34:46.448 --> 34:47.531
- Get back in the car,
we're, what,

34:47.615 --> 34:48.782
two, three hours from Marvin's?

34:48.865 --> 34:52.073
- We're here, damnit.
We have every right to be.

34:52.156 --> 34:53.907
We're citizens.

34:53.989 --> 34:56.156
You're a veteran
for God's sake.

34:56.239 --> 34:58.907
Our money spends just as good
as everyone else's.

34:58.989 --> 35:01.989
[low ominous notes]

35:05.031 --> 35:06.865
- I gotta visit
the ladies' room.

35:15.323 --> 35:18.323
- Biscuits and gravy
did smell pretty damn good.

35:19.323 --> 35:21.782
Think I'll order that...

35:21.865 --> 35:24.490
if the waiter ever comes back.

35:27.156 --> 35:28.989
- There's three of them.

35:29.073 --> 35:31.573
Just sat down.

35:34.907 --> 35:36.782
I swear I didn't serve them,

35:36.865 --> 35:39.448
not after what you did
to Ms. Lydia.

35:39.531 --> 35:42.448
[suspenseful music]

35:42.531 --> 35:49.531
♪ ♪

35:52.365 --> 35:55.156
- Uncle George?
- Hmm?

35:58.323 --> 36:00.573
- Remind me why
the White House is white.

36:03.365 --> 36:05.156
- War of 1812.

36:05.239 --> 36:08.823
British soldiers put
the executive branch to torch,

36:08.907 --> 36:11.490
and later,
when the slaves rebuilt it,

36:11.573 --> 36:12.657
they had to paint
the walls white

36:12.740 --> 36:14.156
to cover up the--
both: Burn marks.

36:14.239 --> 36:15.657
[siren wailing]

36:15.740 --> 36:17.281
- Get your ass up!
We gotta get the fuck

36:17.365 --> 36:19.948
outta here now!

36:20.031 --> 36:21.823
- Come on, come on, George.
Come on!

36:21.907 --> 36:23.323
Out.
[tires squealing]

36:23.406 --> 36:27.323
[intense music]

36:27.406 --> 36:28.615
- Let me drive.

36:28.698 --> 36:30.156
- Get your ass in the car!

36:30.239 --> 36:31.198
- Come on, come on,
come on, come on.

36:31.281 --> 36:33.365
[siren wailing]

36:33.448 --> 36:35.448
[gunshot]

36:37.698 --> 36:39.239
[gunshot]

36:44.114 --> 36:45.323
[bullets ricocheting]

36:45.406 --> 36:46.865
[tires screech]

36:46.948 --> 36:48.907
[horn blares]

36:50.948 --> 36:51.865
[gunshots]

36:51.948 --> 36:53.573
- Keep it steady!
- We're being shot at!

36:53.657 --> 36:55.698
How the hell am I supposed
to keep it steady?

36:55.782 --> 36:58.531
- [groans]
- [yells]

36:58.615 --> 37:05.615
♪ ♪

37:08.989 --> 37:10.989
- They're gaining on us!

37:11.073 --> 37:13.448
- Take this left up ahead.

37:14.615 --> 37:16.073
- Slow down,
or Woody will spin out.

37:16.156 --> 37:17.907
- Oh, just shut up
and let me drive.

37:17.989 --> 37:20.406
[tires screech]

37:20.490 --> 37:21.740
- Damnit, girl,
you're gonna crash us.

37:21.823 --> 37:24.281
- My name's not "girl."
It's Letitia fucking Lewis!

37:26.156 --> 37:29.073
[dramatic music]

37:29.156 --> 37:34.531
♪ ♪

37:34.615 --> 37:37.156
- Go, get on up there!

37:40.323 --> 37:42.573
Get up on these
sons of bitches!

37:42.657 --> 37:44.823
[glass shatters]

37:47.989 --> 37:49.657
- Leti.
- I see it.

37:52.740 --> 37:54.490
- [yells]
- Shit.

37:55.490 --> 37:57.865
[engine revs]

37:57.948 --> 37:59.865
- Hit it!

37:59.948 --> 38:06.989
♪ ♪

38:09.698 --> 38:11.698
- [screams]

38:21.531 --> 38:24.448
[tense music]

38:24.531 --> 38:29.448
♪ ♪

38:29.531 --> 38:30.948
- Go.

38:31.031 --> 38:33.573
Go, Leti, go!

38:53.406 --> 38:56.698
[laughter]
Stop.

38:56.782 --> 38:59.865
- And the way
those white boys went flying.

38:59.948 --> 39:01.448
- It was surreal.
- Reminds me of a scene

39:01.531 --> 39:02.657
out of a Bradbury novel.

39:02.740 --> 39:04.823
[laughter]

39:04.907 --> 39:07.406
- Wait, what actually happened
that caused the crash?

39:10.281 --> 39:12.948
- Your sister's
precision driving.

39:13.031 --> 39:14.323
They couldn't keep up.

39:14.406 --> 39:16.156
- She did save the day.

39:16.239 --> 39:18.531
- Wait, wait, now, now, now.
Say that again one more time.

39:18.615 --> 39:20.948
Did I hear that right?
Who saved your asses?

39:21.031 --> 39:22.323
- Letitia fucking Lewis.

39:22.406 --> 39:24.031
- [laughs]

39:24.114 --> 39:25.406
- It's getting late, Marvin.

39:25.490 --> 39:28.365
Why don't you tell us what you
discovered about our next stop?

39:28.448 --> 39:30.615
- Well, I heard a few tales
about Devon County before,

39:30.698 --> 39:32.073
but once I started
really digging in,

39:32.156 --> 39:34.865
it just kept getting
stranger and stranger.

39:34.948 --> 39:37.073
You see,
the county seat, Bideford,

39:37.156 --> 39:38.365
is named after
a town in England

39:38.448 --> 39:40.823
where they had
one of the last witch trials.

39:40.907 --> 39:42.698
They hung a woman
for fornicating with the devil

39:42.782 --> 39:45.782
who appeared to her
as a Negro man.

39:45.865 --> 39:48.198
- Y-you're saying that Bideford

39:48.281 --> 39:49.490
was founded by witches?

39:49.573 --> 39:51.448
- No, the witch hunters,

39:51.531 --> 39:54.198
and they don't like
outsiders at all.

39:54.281 --> 39:55.989
I found more than a few stories
in our morgue

39:56.073 --> 39:58.823
about travelers being attacked
in the surrounding woods.

39:58.907 --> 40:00.448
By what?
- Grizzles, wolves.

40:00.531 --> 40:01.657
Who knows?

40:01.740 --> 40:05.573
There's been a bunch
of missing person stories, too,

40:05.657 --> 40:09.907
some of which might be due
to the current sheriff.

40:09.989 --> 40:12.073
- Eustice Hunt.

40:12.156 --> 40:14.114
Ex-Marine.

40:14.198 --> 40:16.615
This is his NAACP
complaint file.

40:16.698 --> 40:19.073
- It's only a third of it.

40:19.156 --> 40:20.615
Between the wild animals
and this guy,

40:20.698 --> 40:22.573
I don't know
who I'd rather run into.

40:22.657 --> 40:24.031
- Hmm.

40:27.615 --> 40:29.740
- What about Ardham?

40:29.823 --> 40:32.239
It was settled around
the same time as Bideford.

40:32.323 --> 40:34.281
Local histories
don't say by who.

40:34.365 --> 40:35.531
- That's what you dug up?

40:35.615 --> 40:37.615
- Yeah, I even tried calling
the county record of deeds

40:37.698 --> 40:39.573
to get the property records.

40:39.657 --> 40:41.365
No one answered.

40:41.448 --> 40:43.948
But from what
I could pull together...

40:46.448 --> 40:48.156
Should be somewhere
right around here.

40:49.823 --> 40:52.114
- That right there
is the middle of nowhere

40:52.198 --> 40:53.865
with no guide stops.

40:56.031 --> 40:57.365
What do you want to do?

41:01.907 --> 41:04.782
- We need to go
to the registry.

41:04.865 --> 41:07.073
Maps of the property line
should clearly delineate

41:07.156 --> 41:10.114
a route in Ardham.

41:10.198 --> 41:13.114
[ominous music]

41:13.198 --> 41:15.448
- Now,
this is just the first issue,

41:15.531 --> 41:17.782
but the plan is
she'll be called to repair

41:17.865 --> 41:19.114
faulty telescopes

41:19.198 --> 41:21.615
or malfunctioning computers
on different planets.

41:21.698 --> 41:23.281
And guess what.

41:23.365 --> 41:25.907
She zips from planet to planet
in her trusted

41:25.989 --> 41:28.073
Buick space wagon named Stoney.

41:28.156 --> 41:29.698
[chuckles]

41:31.698 --> 41:33.031
Pop?

41:33.114 --> 41:37.782
Pop, are you there?
- Ye--yes, I'm--yes.

41:37.865 --> 41:39.323
It all sounds great,

41:39.406 --> 41:40.698
but, honey, I gotta go.

41:40.782 --> 41:44.281
I-I don't want to run up
Mr. Baptiste's bill.

41:44.365 --> 41:45.865
Now, put your mother
back on the phone.

41:45.948 --> 41:47.823
- All right, Pop.

41:47.907 --> 41:50.323
Mom.

41:50.406 --> 41:52.114
- I was just headed
to the roof.

41:53.573 --> 41:55.281
Such a clear night,
I might finally

41:55.365 --> 41:57.031
get to see Cassiopeia.

41:57.114 --> 41:58.073
- Mm-hmm.

41:59.907 --> 42:01.865
Well, I-I don't want
to keep you.

42:03.657 --> 42:05.657
But, honey, I was...

42:05.740 --> 42:07.406
I was thinking.

42:10.073 --> 42:12.448
Maybe for the next guide trip,

42:12.531 --> 42:15.989
what do you say you and I,
we go together?

42:17.573 --> 42:20.490
[heartfelt music]

42:20.573 --> 42:27.573
♪ ♪

42:29.573 --> 42:31.573
- I'd like that.

42:36.114 --> 42:39.198
Good night, George Freeman.

42:39.281 --> 42:40.406
- Good night.

42:40.490 --> 42:47.448
♪ ♪

43:24.323 --> 43:25.490
- So how long
is your little visit

43:25.573 --> 43:26.740
supposed to last this time?

43:26.823 --> 43:29.073
- I'll be home in a few weeks.
I'll pull my own weight.

43:29.156 --> 43:30.490
Do some cooking,
some cleaning--

43:30.573 --> 43:31.865
- What did you do
with the money

43:31.948 --> 43:33.907
that I sent to you in D.C.
two months ago?

43:33.989 --> 43:35.114
- I saved it, Marvin.

43:35.198 --> 43:37.239
It's what I used
to get the bus to Ruby.

43:37.323 --> 43:40.281
- Not all of it, you didn't.
I'm not stupid, Letitia.

43:40.365 --> 43:42.239
- Fine.
All right, I used it

43:42.323 --> 43:44.073
to bail some friends
out of jail,

43:44.156 --> 43:45.114
but it's not what you think.

43:45.198 --> 43:46.198
- It never is with you!

43:46.281 --> 43:47.490
- We were protesting
the school--

43:47.573 --> 43:49.782
- It doesn't matter
what you were doing!

43:49.865 --> 43:52.114
- The work I'm doing
is saving lives, Marvin!

43:52.198 --> 43:54.198
- You told me you needed money

43:54.281 --> 43:55.823
because you needed
to come home.

43:55.907 --> 43:57.073
And I thought
I gave you the money

43:57.156 --> 43:59.156
so you could come home
for Mama's funeral.

43:59.239 --> 44:01.156
How could you miss your
own Mama's funeral, Letitia?

44:01.239 --> 44:04.615
- Hell. Y'all gonna continue
to throw that in my face.

44:04.698 --> 44:06.239
- Absolutely! It's our mama!
- You and Ruby

44:06.323 --> 44:08.073
want to act
like she's a goddamn saint.

44:08.156 --> 44:09.114
I'm sick and tired of it.

44:09.198 --> 44:10.948
- Now, you watch your mouth
in my house

44:11.031 --> 44:11.907
talking about our mama!

44:11.989 --> 44:12.989
- But you know what?
I can understand

44:13.073 --> 44:14.323
you wanting
to think that about her

44:14.406 --> 44:15.948
because you didn't
have to live with her!

44:16.031 --> 44:17.782
- Hey, I went to Chicago
every summer.

44:17.865 --> 44:19.989
- Oh, every summer!
You got to come down here--

44:20.073 --> 44:22.448
- [sighs]

44:22.531 --> 44:23.823
- Ruby and I
didn't have that option.

44:23.907 --> 44:25.323
- Well, you say that
like it was my fault.

44:25.406 --> 44:26.989
- It's not sounding good.

44:27.073 --> 44:29.323
- Don't give me a fucking
lecture about Mama.

44:29.406 --> 44:31.323
- I've heard worse.

44:31.406 --> 44:33.323
[arguing continues]

44:33.406 --> 44:35.989
Been a part of worse.

44:36.073 --> 44:38.448
- We're impossible?
- Yes.

44:38.531 --> 44:42.156
- Pops tell you what happened
last time I was home?

44:42.239 --> 44:43.406
- No.

44:44.989 --> 44:47.948
- Reporter came by.

44:48.031 --> 44:50.657
Wanted to interview me
on what it was like

44:50.740 --> 44:54.323
to be a Negro soldier.

44:54.406 --> 44:56.823
Pops lost it.

44:56.907 --> 44:58.989
Said it was bad enough
I was throwing my life away

44:59.073 --> 45:01.239
for a country that hates me.

45:02.323 --> 45:03.865
Now, I was gonna go
inspire others

45:03.948 --> 45:06.448
to make the same
stupid mistake.

45:10.657 --> 45:14.198
I decided to give as good
as I got for once.

45:14.281 --> 45:15.865
Still see the cracks
in the plaster

45:15.948 --> 45:17.239
where we slammed into the wall.

45:17.323 --> 45:20.239
- Just because he didn't agree
with the decision

45:20.323 --> 45:21.698
doesn't mean he didn't care.

45:21.782 --> 45:24.239
- [scoffs]
He never wrote me.

45:28.448 --> 45:30.573
Not one letter
till he needed help.

45:30.657 --> 45:33.198
- Your first year in Korea,
he'd come by for dinner

45:33.281 --> 45:34.531
almost every night.

45:34.615 --> 45:36.031
Wouldn't ask about you,

45:36.114 --> 45:38.740
but he'd wait for me
to volunteer the information.

45:38.823 --> 45:41.698
If I didn't,
he wouldn't go home.

45:41.782 --> 45:45.948
He'd stay till 10:00,
11:00, midnight,

45:46.031 --> 45:47.573
if that's what it took,
waiting for me

45:47.657 --> 45:51.657
to bring up
the subject of you.

45:51.740 --> 45:52.907
Drove Hippolyta crazy.

45:52.989 --> 45:55.114
- Course it did.

45:55.198 --> 45:57.281
Just another example
of how hardheaded he was.

45:57.365 --> 46:00.198
- Montrose has done
the best he can.

46:00.281 --> 46:01.573
He didn't have it easy
with our father.

46:01.657 --> 46:04.031
- Why are you
always defending him?

46:04.114 --> 46:07.948
You grew up in the same house.
You came out just fine.

46:08.031 --> 46:09.573
- Your pops was...

46:09.657 --> 46:11.448
- Was what?

46:12.615 --> 46:13.782
What?

46:13.865 --> 46:16.073
- He was younger.

46:16.156 --> 46:19.239
He was smaller.
He took the brunt of it.

46:19.323 --> 46:22.406
I should've protected him more.
I always regret that.

46:22.490 --> 46:24.490
- I was younger and smaller,
too.

46:26.406 --> 46:27.615
- You ain't do shit
to protect me.

46:27.698 --> 46:29.698
You regret that?

46:31.698 --> 46:32.907
[glass breaks]

46:32.989 --> 46:34.948
- God damn it!
Look at what you made me do!

46:35.031 --> 46:37.573
- Atticus.

46:37.657 --> 46:39.615
It's family business.
- Let go of my arm.

46:39.698 --> 46:41.156
You're hurting me.
- It's not ours.

46:41.239 --> 46:43.782
- Go! I don't want you
in my house another night!

46:43.865 --> 46:45.740
[door slams]

46:45.823 --> 46:48.823
[thunder rumbling]

46:53.031 --> 46:55.281
- [sighs]

46:55.365 --> 46:58.615
[thunder booming]

46:58.698 --> 47:01.490
[dramatic music]

47:01.573 --> 47:08.573
♪ ♪

47:19.114 --> 47:26.073
♪ ♪

47:35.615 --> 47:42.573
♪ ♪

47:46.740 --> 47:49.740
[ominous music]

47:49.823 --> 47:56.782
♪ ♪

47:57.782 --> 48:00.198
- We done passed
this area ten times now.

48:00.281 --> 48:01.657
- Map at the registry said
there's a bridge

48:01.740 --> 48:02.657
over the river to Ardham--

48:02.740 --> 48:04.323
- I know what it says.
- It exists.

48:04.406 --> 48:05.365
We just gotta find
the road to it.

48:05.448 --> 48:07.198
- We've been driving
these woods all day.

48:07.281 --> 48:08.573
There's no damn road.

48:08.657 --> 48:10.031
Letitia,
you done seen something?

48:10.114 --> 48:11.865
- Nah, I ain't seen--
- Stop the car.

48:11.948 --> 48:12.989
Stop the car.
I'll get out and look.

48:13.073 --> 48:14.698
- So you can look for a road
that none of us

48:14.782 --> 48:15.907
has stopped all damn day?

48:15.989 --> 48:17.865
- Maybe it's grown over.
You ever think of that?

48:17.948 --> 48:20.573
Maybe that's why we missed it.
Just pull over.

48:27.281 --> 48:29.073
Shit. Shit!

48:30.657 --> 48:31.740
What are you doing?

48:31.823 --> 48:33.823
- Helping you look.

48:35.865 --> 48:37.740
Been thinking
about what my brother said.

48:37.823 --> 48:39.448
I don't think we want to be
out here after dark.

48:39.531 --> 48:41.114
- I know.

48:41.198 --> 48:42.865
[sighs]

48:42.948 --> 48:44.031
Just we come all this way.

48:44.114 --> 48:45.865
- [sighs]
This isn't giving up.

48:45.948 --> 48:48.239
We're gonna find your father.

48:48.323 --> 48:49.323
Just not today.

48:49.406 --> 48:51.073
[branches rustling]

48:51.156 --> 48:53.114
What was that?

48:54.531 --> 48:56.406
- It's a shoggoth.

48:56.490 --> 48:58.073
- What?

48:58.156 --> 49:01.073
- It's a monster from one
of Lovecraft's stories.

49:01.156 --> 49:03.073
- And what do they look like?

49:03.156 --> 49:06.114
- Massive bubble blob
with hundreds of eyes.

49:06.198 --> 49:08.239
- Oh, well,
that's not scary at all.

49:08.323 --> 49:09.782
We can outrun a blob.

49:09.865 --> 49:12.198
- Uncle George can't.
[both laughing]

49:12.281 --> 49:14.156
- He cannot.

49:14.239 --> 49:17.156
[dramatic music]

49:17.239 --> 49:21.823
♪ ♪

49:21.907 --> 49:23.989
- You in the car, get out.

49:24.073 --> 49:26.989
And everybody come round
to the back of the vehicle.

49:37.740 --> 49:39.865
- It's all right.

49:44.031 --> 49:45.114
- Who are you?

49:45.198 --> 49:47.448
- George Freeman, sir.
This here is my nephew Atticus

49:47.531 --> 49:48.615
and his friend Letitia.

49:48.698 --> 49:51.073
- Where y'all from?
- Chicago, sir.

49:51.156 --> 49:52.239
- You're a long way from home.

49:52.323 --> 49:53.531
- Oh,
we're just passing through,

49:53.615 --> 49:56.281
taking a little bathroom break,
sir, is all.

49:57.657 --> 49:59.907
- Any of you all know
what a sundown town is?

50:01.615 --> 50:03.698
- Yes, sir.
We do.

50:03.782 --> 50:06.198
- Well,
this is a sundown county.

50:06.281 --> 50:08.698
If I had found you
pissing in my woods

50:08.782 --> 50:10.907
like animals after dark,

50:10.989 --> 50:12.323
it would've been my sworn duty

50:12.406 --> 50:14.823
to hang every single one of you
from them trees.

50:14.907 --> 50:16.782
- It's not sundown yet.

50:23.239 --> 50:25.989
- Sunset is at 7:09 today.

50:26.073 --> 50:27.657
That's seven minutes from now.

50:27.740 --> 50:29.782
- Then we'll be
out of the county in six.

50:29.865 --> 50:31.323
- Now, that's impossible
heading south

50:31.406 --> 50:33.198
on the road
you're currently on,

50:33.281 --> 50:35.031
unless you were to speed.

50:35.114 --> 50:36.865
And if you were to speed,
I'd have to pull you over.

50:36.948 --> 50:38.782
- Then we'll head north.

50:43.490 --> 50:44.989
- That might work.

50:45.073 --> 50:46.365
Why don't you give it a try?

50:46.448 --> 50:48.156
- We will, sir.

50:51.406 --> 50:53.573
- Is it legal
to make a U-turn here?

50:55.782 --> 50:57.698
- Aren't you a smart one?

50:57.782 --> 50:59.490
Now, ordinarily,
I would consider

50:59.573 --> 51:01.490
a U-turn a violation.

51:01.573 --> 51:03.698
But if you ask me real nice,

51:03.782 --> 51:07.073
I might just
let it go this time.

51:07.156 --> 51:08.323
- Please.

51:08.406 --> 51:10.823
- Oh,
you can do better than that.

51:10.907 --> 51:14.198
Say, "pretty please,

51:14.281 --> 51:17.490
will you let this smart nigger
make a U-turn here?"

51:22.448 --> 51:25.323
- Pretty please,
will you let this smart nigger

51:25.406 --> 51:26.989
make a U-turn here?

51:32.989 --> 51:34.907
- All right.

51:34.989 --> 51:38.698
Just this one time,
since you asked so nicely.

51:46.823 --> 51:49.782
[engine revving]

51:49.865 --> 51:51.239
- How far, Uncle George?

51:51.323 --> 51:53.989
- We got 2 1/2 kilometers
to the county line.

51:54.073 --> 51:55.114
- Can we make that?
- Wait, wait, I--

51:55.198 --> 51:56.198
wait, I'm sorry--we...

51:56.281 --> 51:59.406
[stammers] 3.
We gotta pass the train tracks.

52:01.698 --> 52:02.615
- What time is it?

52:02.698 --> 52:04.448
- It's, uh, it's 7--7:05.

52:04.531 --> 52:05.782
- Can we make it
in four minutes?

52:05.865 --> 52:07.615
- We have to.

52:07.698 --> 52:11.281
[dark, suspenseful music]

52:11.365 --> 52:13.281
- Here he comes!
- Shit.

52:13.365 --> 52:17.156
[engine chugs]

52:17.239 --> 52:21.073
♪ ♪

52:21.156 --> 52:22.823
- Can you go faster?
- No, we can't go faster.

52:22.907 --> 52:23.948
He gonna pull us over.

52:24.031 --> 52:26.948
[suspenseful music]

52:27.031 --> 52:33.281
♪ ♪

52:33.365 --> 52:37.448
[engine revving]

52:37.531 --> 52:38.907
- He's speedin' up.
- What's he doin'?

52:38.989 --> 52:39.989
- I don't know!

52:40.073 --> 52:42.989
[engine revving]

52:43.073 --> 52:45.365
- Crazy bastard!
- Son of a bitch!

52:45.448 --> 52:46.865
He's comin' again!

52:49.031 --> 52:50.239
- Hold on.

52:57.782 --> 52:58.865
Leti, get the gun.

53:01.073 --> 53:03.073
[gun clicking]

53:05.073 --> 53:07.198
- We got a minute.

53:07.281 --> 53:10.198
[dark music]

53:10.281 --> 53:17.281
♪ ♪

53:30.448 --> 53:33.156
- [murmuring under breath]

53:33.239 --> 53:36.031
[dark, suspenseful music]

53:36.114 --> 53:42.281
♪ ♪

53:43.615 --> 53:45.531
- There's the tracks!

53:45.615 --> 53:47.031
- Atticus, watch your speed!

53:47.114 --> 53:48.198
- How much time left?

53:48.281 --> 53:49.198
- 30 seconds.

53:49.281 --> 53:51.657
[engine revving]

53:51.740 --> 53:57.907
♪ ♪

53:57.989 --> 53:59.657
10 seconds!

53:59.740 --> 54:01.365
- Come on! Come on!

54:01.448 --> 54:08.490
♪ ♪

54:16.323 --> 54:17.698
- Ah!
- Hell.

54:17.782 --> 54:20.114
Hell. Hell.

54:22.490 --> 54:24.239
- Yeah.
- Okay, Tic.

54:24.323 --> 54:25.239
- Ha ha!

54:25.323 --> 54:28.573
- We did it. Whoo!

54:28.657 --> 54:30.948
[ominous music]

54:31.031 --> 54:32.948
- Oh, shit.

54:33.031 --> 54:36.281
♪ ♪

54:36.365 --> 54:38.198
[rifles click]

54:38.281 --> 54:45.323
♪ ♪

54:50.323 --> 54:53.365
- I knew they'd strike again
tonight.

54:53.448 --> 54:55.448
- You said they'd be Gypsies,
Sheriff.

54:55.531 --> 54:57.740
- Oh, they're travelers,
that's for sure.

54:57.823 --> 54:59.948
- Unless the car's stolen.

55:00.031 --> 55:03.907
- [laughing]
That's a fair point, Talbert.

55:05.031 --> 55:07.448
How 'bout that? Hmm?

55:07.531 --> 55:08.948
You really from Illinois?

55:09.031 --> 55:10.782
- This is a misunderstanding.

55:10.865 --> 55:11.948
I don't know who you all were
lyin' in wait for--

55:12.031 --> 55:13.156
- Get 'em on the ground!

55:13.239 --> 55:14.239
- Aah!

55:14.323 --> 55:15.782
- [grunts]

55:15.865 --> 55:18.323
- Let me just finish
the rest for you.

55:18.406 --> 55:22.948
When I ask you about a burglary
in Bideford last night

55:23.031 --> 55:25.156
or two others
in Bucks Mill last week,

55:25.239 --> 55:27.698
you're gonna say to me,
"What burglaries, Sheriff?

55:27.782 --> 55:29.323
We're just passin' through."

55:29.406 --> 55:31.823
[officers chuckling]

55:31.907 --> 55:33.031
- Sheriff Hunt.
[rifles cocking]

55:36.989 --> 55:37.865
- My uncle's right.

55:37.948 --> 55:39.198
This is just
a misunderstanding.

55:39.281 --> 55:42.239
We're not burglars
or car thieves.

55:42.323 --> 55:43.281
You're more than welcome
to check the car

55:43.365 --> 55:45.448
for stolen goods if you like.

55:46.531 --> 55:48.865
- Dalton, tell me I didn't just
hear that.

55:48.948 --> 55:52.615
Did this nigger give me
permission to search his car?

55:52.698 --> 55:54.782
- I believe he did, Sheriff.

55:54.865 --> 55:56.531
- This one thinks he's smart.

55:57.573 --> 56:00.989
Then tell me,
if you're just passin' through,

56:01.073 --> 56:02.531
why do you know my name?

56:04.239 --> 56:05.239
[rifle cocks]

56:05.323 --> 56:07.323
- [yelling] Answer me!
- Answer, boy!

56:07.406 --> 56:10.740
- Please, please--
[overlapping pleading]

56:10.823 --> 56:14.865
[chittering, rustling]

56:14.948 --> 56:16.365
- What was that?

56:16.448 --> 56:18.198
- All right,
keep your guns on 'em--

56:18.281 --> 56:19.907
it's probably just wolves.

56:19.989 --> 56:20.989
[snarling, chittering]

56:21.073 --> 56:22.740
- That don't sound like fuckin'
wolves, Sheriff.

56:22.823 --> 56:24.657
[thud]

56:24.740 --> 56:27.657
[chittering]

56:27.740 --> 56:30.698
[rustling, shrieking]

56:30.782 --> 56:33.573
[crickets chirping]

56:36.823 --> 56:38.073
[roaring]
- Aah!

56:38.156 --> 56:39.490
- Jesus--

56:39.573 --> 56:41.156
[loud gibbering, gunshots]

56:41.239 --> 56:42.365
- Run!

56:42.448 --> 56:45.031
[gibbering, gunfire continue]

56:45.114 --> 56:46.531
- Aah!

56:46.615 --> 56:47.573
- Run!

56:47.657 --> 56:48.989
- Aah!

56:49.073 --> 56:52.989
[gibbering, snarling continue]

56:53.073 --> 56:57.281
- Go! Run! Run! Go!

56:58.156 --> 57:00.615
[creature shrieks]

57:00.698 --> 57:03.073
- There!
We need to get out in the open!

57:03.156 --> 57:04.281
Aah!

57:06.698 --> 57:07.989
- Get up!

57:09.031 --> 57:10.698
- I'm comin' down!

57:10.782 --> 57:14.448
[snarling, gibbering continue]

57:14.531 --> 57:16.698
[roar]

57:16.782 --> 57:20.073
[gunshot]
- Aah!

57:20.156 --> 57:22.198
- Go, go, go!

57:23.782 --> 57:26.740
Wait!
Where's Uncle George?

57:26.823 --> 57:28.073
- Get in here!

57:28.156 --> 57:30.782
[thudding, gibbering continue]

57:30.865 --> 57:32.615
- It's coming to your right!

57:32.698 --> 57:33.615
[gunshot]

57:33.698 --> 57:36.490
[distant shouting]

57:36.573 --> 57:38.657
[gunshot]

57:38.740 --> 57:41.448
[gibbering, shrieking]

57:41.531 --> 57:45.156
[gunshots,
voices grow more distant]

57:45.239 --> 57:48.239
- [whimpering]

57:49.239 --> 57:51.406
- Aah!

57:51.490 --> 57:53.573
[gunshots]

57:53.657 --> 57:56.573
[loud screech, chittering]

57:56.657 --> 57:59.615
- Sheriff, come on! Come o--
open this fucking door!

57:59.698 --> 58:00.615
[pounding on door]

58:00.698 --> 58:04.156
- Open this fucking door!
Stay back!

58:04.239 --> 58:06.531
[gunshot blast]
- Aah!

58:08.365 --> 58:09.948
- Get back! Get back!

58:10.031 --> 58:11.531
Close the fuckin' door.

58:11.615 --> 58:13.782
Close the fucking door.
[door slams]

58:13.865 --> 58:15.448
- You--
- What?

58:15.531 --> 58:17.657
- Get the fucking table!

58:17.740 --> 58:21.698
[tense music]

58:21.782 --> 58:24.615
- [panting, groaning]

58:24.698 --> 58:27.615
♪ ♪

58:35.031 --> 58:38.657
[soft growling]

58:38.740 --> 58:40.531
[branch cracks,
chittering]

58:48.740 --> 58:51.948
[distant gibbering, screeching]

58:53.865 --> 58:55.782
- He might be okay.

58:57.907 --> 58:59.156
Hell, Tic, you can't--

58:59.239 --> 59:00.156
- I gotta go get him!

59:00.239 --> 59:01.490
- Hey! Wait!

59:01.573 --> 59:02.823
- Shit!

59:02.907 --> 59:04.031
- I'm not risking you leading
those things back here,

59:04.114 --> 59:05.073
you understand?

59:05.156 --> 59:07.365
- What, you gonna shoot me,
hmm?

59:07.448 --> 59:09.156
Gunshot'll bring them things
right to ya.

59:09.239 --> 59:10.531
[panting]

59:10.615 --> 59:11.907
[twigs crack]

59:11.989 --> 59:14.198
- Sheriff,
there's someone comin'.

59:14.281 --> 59:15.531
There's someone comin'.

59:15.615 --> 59:17.406
- Uncle George!
- Open the door!

59:17.490 --> 59:18.823
Come on!

59:18.907 --> 59:20.198
- Get this shit out the way!

59:20.281 --> 59:21.531
- What are you doing? No!

59:21.615 --> 59:23.531
- Uncle George?

59:23.615 --> 59:25.323
- Come on!

59:25.406 --> 59:27.573
- Quick! Close the door!

59:27.657 --> 59:28.698
- Are you all right?

59:28.782 --> 59:30.365
- Depends on your definition
of all right.

59:30.448 --> 59:31.698
- I thought you were right
behind us.

59:31.782 --> 59:33.156
- I got knocked down and stayed
down till the coast was clear.

59:33.239 --> 59:34.531
- Aren't you a lucky nigger?

59:34.615 --> 59:36.198
Those things got four
of my men.

59:36.281 --> 59:38.406
- What are those things?
They tore that man's head off!

59:38.490 --> 59:40.782
- They're monsters!
- Monsters don't fuckin' exist!

59:40.865 --> 59:42.073
- It doesn't matter
what they are!

59:42.156 --> 59:43.948
We need to fight 'em!
All right? We need weapons!

59:44.031 --> 59:46.948
[clattering, thudding]

59:47.031 --> 59:50.365
[roaring, chittering,
screeching]

59:52.989 --> 59:54.365
- Listen to 'em.

59:54.448 --> 59:57.239
"Children of the night...
what music they make."

59:57.323 --> 59:58.865
- What is he muttering
on about?

59:58.948 --> 1:00:00.114
- It's a quote from "Dracula."

1:00:00.198 --> 1:00:01.531
- None of them attacked me,

1:00:01.615 --> 1:00:03.073
and all I had
is this flashlight.

1:00:03.156 --> 1:00:04.740
- You think those things
are like vampires.

1:00:04.823 --> 1:00:06.948
- If I'm right,
and the light hurts them,

1:00:07.031 --> 1:00:08.907
it'll also explain why
we been drivin' in the woods

1:00:08.989 --> 1:00:12.073
all day and didn't encounter
one until the sun went down.

1:00:12.156 --> 1:00:13.406
- So we just need to survive
till sunup.

1:00:13.490 --> 1:00:14.406
- Yes.

1:00:14.490 --> 1:00:15.406
- And find more light
till then.

1:00:15.490 --> 1:00:16.573
- Yes.
- And there's flares in Woody.

1:00:16.657 --> 1:00:17.782
- And the headlights
would help too.

1:00:17.865 --> 1:00:20.823
- Where's the car from here?
Where's the car from here!

1:00:20.907 --> 1:00:22.490
- A quarter mile through
the woods behind the cabin.

1:00:22.573 --> 1:00:24.281
- I'll go.
I'll make a run for it.

1:00:24.365 --> 1:00:26.615
- No! No, you don't.

1:00:26.698 --> 1:00:28.323
You're too smart
for your own good.

1:00:28.406 --> 1:00:29.865
You might get the idea
in your head

1:00:29.948 --> 1:00:31.156
to leave us behind.

1:00:32.657 --> 1:00:34.448
[panting] She goes.

1:00:34.531 --> 1:00:35.907
- Not a chance in hell.
[cocks shotgun]

1:00:35.989 --> 1:00:38.281
- Leti.
- I am not asking.

1:00:38.365 --> 1:00:40.281
- Fuck you!
- No, I can--I can go!

1:00:40.365 --> 1:00:42.323
I can go, I can do it.
I can do it, Tic.

1:00:42.406 --> 1:00:44.281
I was all-star track
in high school, remember?

1:00:44.365 --> 1:00:45.615
Plus, I know you say you don't
need those glasses

1:00:45.698 --> 1:00:47.073
to drive at night,
but I really don't think

1:00:47.156 --> 1:00:49.406
this is the time to test it!

1:00:55.531 --> 1:00:58.114
- All right.

1:00:58.198 --> 1:01:01.698
You run as fast as you can.
No lookin' back.

1:01:01.782 --> 1:01:03.490
You hear gunshots,
you don't come back.

1:01:03.573 --> 1:01:04.657
You drive for help.

1:01:04.740 --> 1:01:05.823
- [murmuring]

1:01:05.907 --> 1:01:07.198
I walk through the valley
of the shadow of death.

1:01:07.281 --> 1:01:09.657
- Leti.
Leti, you hear me?

1:01:09.740 --> 1:01:11.531
- Yes, I fucking hear you.
I'm terrified!

1:01:11.615 --> 1:01:13.323
You don't even seem scared.

1:01:13.406 --> 1:01:15.281
Where they teach you that--
in the army?

1:01:16.698 --> 1:01:19.823
- I'm not scared 'cause fear's
not gonna save us right now.

1:01:19.907 --> 1:01:21.031
You are.

1:01:23.198 --> 1:01:25.365
Come on.
Come on.

1:01:25.448 --> 1:01:26.823
Go, run, run, run!

1:01:26.907 --> 1:01:29.907
[gibbering, shrieking]

1:01:33.239 --> 1:01:34.323
- And I'll take that flashlight

1:01:34.406 --> 1:01:36.323
just in case
your theory is correct.

1:01:36.406 --> 1:01:39.448
[tense music]

1:01:39.531 --> 1:01:40.865
♪ ♪

1:01:40.948 --> 1:01:43.490
- [panting, grunting]

1:01:47.114 --> 1:01:49.114
[loud snarling]

1:01:54.698 --> 1:01:58.782
- [grunts, coughing]

1:02:05.114 --> 1:02:06.490
- Where the fuck is she?

1:02:06.573 --> 1:02:08.740
- Atticus.
Atticus.

1:02:08.823 --> 1:02:12.782
- [continues coughing,
snarling]

1:02:12.865 --> 1:02:14.365
- Sheriff, you okay?

1:02:14.448 --> 1:02:17.031
- What happens when you get
bitten by a vampire?

1:02:17.114 --> 1:02:20.323
- [continues gagging,
snarling]

1:02:20.406 --> 1:02:21.698
- Aah!

1:02:21.782 --> 1:02:25.740
- [whimpering, panting]

1:02:25.823 --> 1:02:28.281
[loud snarling]

1:02:28.365 --> 1:02:29.615
[screams]

1:02:34.365 --> 1:02:36.114
[galloping footsteps]
- Come on, come on, come on!

1:02:36.198 --> 1:02:37.406
[engine struggles]

1:02:37.490 --> 1:02:39.406
- [snarling]

1:02:39.490 --> 1:02:40.490
- What the fuck?

1:02:40.573 --> 1:02:43.406
- You--you need to shoot him.

1:02:43.490 --> 1:02:44.573
- [loud snarling]

1:02:44.657 --> 1:02:45.740
- Shoot the motherfucker!

1:02:45.823 --> 1:02:46.907
- Come on, come on--
[engine struggling]

1:02:46.989 --> 1:02:48.698
[creature roars]

1:02:48.782 --> 1:02:49.948
- Aah!

1:02:50.031 --> 1:02:50.948
[creature shrieks]

1:02:51.031 --> 1:02:52.031
- Oh! Oh!

1:02:52.114 --> 1:02:53.323
Oh...

1:02:54.323 --> 1:02:55.323
[exhales]

1:02:58.156 --> 1:02:59.114
[thud, roar]

1:02:59.198 --> 1:03:01.615
- Aah!

1:03:01.698 --> 1:03:02.740
- I'll shoot him!
- Shoot him!

1:03:02.823 --> 1:03:04.615
- Shut up!

1:03:04.698 --> 1:03:06.114
Aah!

1:03:06.198 --> 1:03:07.948
- Aah!

1:03:08.031 --> 1:03:09.114
- [snarls]

1:03:09.198 --> 1:03:11.114
- [screaming]

1:03:11.198 --> 1:03:13.031
[bulb pops,
creature shrieks]

1:03:17.365 --> 1:03:18.281
- [snarling]

1:03:18.365 --> 1:03:20.615
- Get the gun!

1:03:20.698 --> 1:03:22.156
Shoot him!

1:03:22.239 --> 1:03:23.156
[gunshot]

1:03:23.239 --> 1:03:24.490
[roars]

1:03:24.573 --> 1:03:25.823
[car horn honking]

1:03:25.907 --> 1:03:27.865
- [roaring, snarling]

1:03:38.823 --> 1:03:40.490
- Whoa--

1:03:40.573 --> 1:03:41.948
[exhales]

1:03:42.031 --> 1:03:45.281
Uncle George?
Uncle George?

1:03:45.365 --> 1:03:47.156
Uncle George!

1:03:47.239 --> 1:03:50.323
[distant gibbering,
roaring]

1:03:50.406 --> 1:03:53.031
- They're coming!

1:03:53.114 --> 1:03:55.198
Get him into the headlights!

1:03:55.281 --> 1:03:59.323
[gibbering, screeching
gets closer]

1:03:59.406 --> 1:04:03.323
- Son of a bitch!
Aah!

1:04:03.406 --> 1:04:06.281
[shrieking, gibbering]

1:04:06.365 --> 1:04:07.531
- Oh, shit!
- Come on.

1:04:07.615 --> 1:04:11.698
[suspenseful music]

1:04:11.782 --> 1:04:14.031
- Oh, shit!

1:04:14.114 --> 1:04:15.657
Yah!

1:04:15.740 --> 1:04:17.156
- [shouts]

1:04:17.239 --> 1:04:21.198
[screeching, roaring continue]

1:04:27.281 --> 1:04:29.698
[intense musical buildup]

1:04:29.782 --> 1:04:33.073
[piercing tone shrieking]

1:04:36.740 --> 1:04:38.114
[monster sounds fade]

1:04:49.907 --> 1:04:52.823
[eerie music]

1:04:52.907 --> 1:04:59.907
♪ ♪

1:05:36.156 --> 1:05:39.114
[intense orchestration]

1:05:39.198 --> 1:05:46.156
♪ ♪

1:06:11.865 --> 1:06:15.490
- We've been expecting you,
Mr. Freeman.

1:06:15.573 --> 1:06:17.573
Welcome home.

1:06:17.657 --> 1:06:24.198
♪ ♪

